            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> ʿǝlat </t:quote></cit>, <lbl expand="pluralis">Pl.</lbl> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʿǝlatāt</t:quote></cit> <sense n="1" xml:id="T1"> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> fate </t:quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወምስለ፡ ብጽሐተ፡ እሉ፡ ልኡካን፡ ወመልእክተ፡ ዚአሆሙ፡ ተሰነአወ፡ ምጽአተ፡ ባሻ፡ እመንገለ፡ ስዋኬን፡ ዘሰሀበቶ፡ ዕለቱ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> Avec l’arrivée de ces messagers et de leur lettre coïncida l’arrivée du bacha, du côté de Sawāken, entraîné par son destin </t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengel"/><citedRange unit="page"> 54 l. 27–28 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengelV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 64 l. 4–5 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">እስመ፡ አእመረት፡ ነፍሱ፡ ለባዊት፡ ከመ፡ ትበጽሖ፡ ይእቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እኁሁ፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> En effet, son esprit intelligent avait compris que le jour de son frère allait l’atteindre </t:quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengel"/><citedRange unit="page"> 92 l. 8–9 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengelV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 105 l. 1–3 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዝንቱኒ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ርቱዓ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ኢቀብጸ፡ ተስፋሁ፡ በእንተዝ፤ አላ፡ አእኮቶ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ እስመ፡ አእመረ፡ ከመ፡ ዕለት፡ ሎቱ፡ ወዕለት፡ ለካልኡ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="it"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> Questo re ortodosso invero non disperò, ma diè lode al Signore, poichè conosceva come vi sarebbe un giorno per lui (prospero), e un giorno per gli altri </t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1894Lebna"/><citedRange unit="page"> 12 l. 15–18 (ed.); 22 l. 33, 23 l. 1–2 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="2" xml:id="T2"><ptr target="#D2"/> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዕለተ፡ ነዛ፡</foreign> probably <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">day of mourning</t:quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወአልቦ፡ ዘተናዘዘ፡ እስከ፡ ዕለተ፡ ነዛ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">no one was consoled until the day of mourning</t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosI"/><citedRange unit="page"> 105 § 229 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosII"/><citedRange unit="page"> 60 § 229 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘<foreign xml:lang="gez">ዕለተ፡ ነዛ፡</foreign> This seems to be the day of the national mourning when the people were crying, wearing black and sprinkling ashes and soil on the hair. The word <foreign xml:lang="am">ነዛ</foreign> is an Amharic loanword which means ‘to drop tears like rainwater.’ The equivalent Gǝʿǝz form of <foreign xml:lang="am">ነዛ</foreign> is <lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <ref type="external" target="https://betamasaheft.eu/Dillmann/lemma/L0e6886d227904bb38c629ffac84c1303"><foreign xml:lang="gez">ነዝኀ</foreign></ref> .’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosII"/><citedRange unit="page"> 60 n. 311</citedRange></bibl>) 
